<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="ie=edge">
    <link type='text/css' href='/stylesheets/style.css' rel='stylesheet'>
    <script src="https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/3.1.1/jquery.min.js"></script>
    <script src="/javascripts/find.js"></script>
    <title>CSDL</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div id="content">
      <div id="top">
        <img src='/images/transparent_bg_white_fg_logo.png' height="75px"/>
      </div>
      <nav>
        <a href="/">Home</a>|
        <a href="/admin">Administration Home</a>|
        <a href="/gamemmr">Change MMR</a>|
        <a href="/playerdata">Modify Player</a>
      </nav>
      <div id="news">
        <div class="title">
          Calibration Management
        </div>
        <p>
          <strong>How Calibration Works</strong><br/><br/>
          Currently calibration works on the basis of the performance of each player in relation to the averages
          recorded by opendota.com. The values are scaled from 0% to 200%. This way we can calibrated the exact amount
          of influence each hero can have on a players MMR during calibration.
          <br/><br/>
          That way there is no Zeus spamming lighning bolts or Oracle spamming Purifying Flames to raise the calibration MMR.
          <br/><br/><strong>Custom Scripts</strong><br/><br/>
          This has yet to be implemented. The purpose is to prevent the MVP complex. This way the carry isn't the only one who gets an MMR boost.
        </p>
        <% for(var i = 0; i < heroes.length; i++) {%>
          <center>
          <div class="cbentry">
            <img src="<%= heroes[i].img %>" height="40px" syle/><br/><h1><%= heroes[i].localized_name %></h1><br/>
            <form method="GET" action="calibration/post">
              <label>GPM:</label><br/>
              <input name="GPM" id="GPM_<%= heroes[i].hero_id %>" type="number" min="0" max="200" step="10" value="<%= heroes[i].GPM_cal %>"/><br/>
              <label>XPM:</label><br/>
              <input name="XPM" id="XPM_<%= heroes[i].hero_id %>" type="number" min="0" max="200" step="10" value="<%= heroes[i].XPM_cal %>"/><br/>
              <label>KPM:</label><br/>
              <input name="KPM" id="KPM_<%= heroes[i].hero_id %>" type="number" min="0" max="200" step="10" value="<%= heroes[i].KPM_cal %>"/><br/>
              <label>LHM:</label><br/>
              <input name="LHM" id="LHM_<%= heroes[i].hero_id %>" type="number" min="0" max="200" step="10" value="<%= heroes[i].LHM_cal %>"/><br/>
              <label>HDM:</label><br/>
              <input name="HDM" id="HDM_<%= heroes[i].hero_id %>" type="number" min="0" max="200" step="10" value="<%= heroes[i].HDM_cal %>"/><br/>
              <label>HHM:</label><br/>
              <input name="HHM" id="HHM_<%= heroes[i].hero_id %>" type="number" min="0" max="200" step="10" value="<%= heroes[i].HHM_cal %>"/><br/>
              <label>TD:</label><br/>
              <input name="TD" id="TD_<%= heroes[i].hero_id %>" type="number" min="0" max="200" step="10" value="<%= heroes[i].TD_cal %>"/><br/>
              <br/><label>Custom Scripts:</label><br/>
              <textarea name="scr" rows="8" cols="20" ><%= heroes[i].scr_cal %></textarea>
              <input name="hid" value="<%= heroes[i].hero_id %>" type="hidden"/>
              <br/><br/><input type="submit" value="Submit"/>
            </form>
          </div>
        </center>
        <% } %>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
